Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Flattened handle, curving. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine light brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.173, 11). Trimmed. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0335.14 and a piece from Kaunos, B.Schmaltz, Die Hellenistischen Amphorenstempel vom Kaunos (Asia Minor Studien 79) 79, KA 182. Name Boiskos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0539)
